text: Vizianagaram district is one of the thirteen districts in the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. The headquarters is Vizianagaram. The French defeated and ended the rule of the Nizam in 1753. These districts were then part of French India. == Related pages == * Vijayanagara architecture == References == Category:1970s establishments in India Category:1979 establishments in Asia Category:Districts of Andhra Pradesh
